# Amplitude Experiment: Product Overview

## Product Overview

Amplitude Experiment is a platform for designing, running, and analyzing controlled experiments (A/B tests and Multi-Armed Bandits) to make data-driven product decisions. The platform enables teams to test hypotheses about product changes by comparing metrics between different user groups and determining statistical significance of observed differences.

### Key Features
- Statistical analysis tools including Welch's T-test
- Experiment design capabilities with configurable parameters
- Sample size and duration estimation
- Real-time monitoring with Cumulative Exposure graphs
- Support for both A/B testing and Multi-Armed Bandit experiments
- Configurable Minimum Detectable Effect (MDE) settings

### Primary Use Cases
- Testing product changes before full deployment
- Measuring the impact of feature modifications on user behavior
- Optimizing conversion rates and other key metrics
- Making data-driven product decisions

